body:
@vlapo

Hi,
Thanks for your input, however I guess the synchronize option is for indices, in my case I want to check uniqueness for the non-index (non-  _id) column. Do you suggest it will work regardless? Please validate.

In some reason `@Column("text", { unique: true })` is not working on mongodb. We should fix this. 

But I think it is no root of @nbaua problem. If you want to check uniqueness you have to enable synchronisation of schema from entity to DB (or synchronize schema first time only) like discussed in https://github.com/typeorm/typeorm/issues/2034 and use workaround:
```typescript
@Index({ unique: true })
@Column("text")
email: string;
```

Keep open this issue as report about problem with unique `@Column("text", { unique: true })` for mongodb. PR is welcome.
